Experiment No.—3 : Altering and Dropping Tables 

a) Alter Table Structure - On table students (id, name, age, department, email). 
Perform the following operations using ALTER TABLE: 
● Add a new column phone of type VARCHAR(15). 
● Modify the data type of age to SMALLINT. 
● Drop the column department from the table. 
b) Rename Table 
Perform the following tasks: 
● Rename the table courses to course_details. 
● Rename the column fees to course_fees inside the same table. 
● Add a new column category with default value 'General'. 
c) Drop Table -  
Perform the following operations: 
● Drop the table enrollments from the database. 
● Recreate a new table enrollments_new (enroll_id, student_id, course_id). 
● Add a new column status with default 'Active' to enrollments_new.

a

ALTER TABLE students
ADD phone VARCHAR(15);

ALTER TABLE students
MODIFY age SMALLINT;

ALTER TABLE students
DROP COLUMN department;

DESC students;

b

RENAME TABLE courses TO course_details;

ALTER TABLE course_details
CHANGE fees course_fees DECIMAL(10,2);

ALTER TABLE course_details
ADD category VARCHAR(50) DEFAULT 'General';

DESC course_details;

c

USE College_DB;

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS enrollments;

CREATE TABLE enrollments_new (
enroll_id INT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
student_id INT,
course_id int
);

ALTER TABLE enrollments_new
ADD status VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'Active';

DESC enrollment_new;
